        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I realize that this would invalidate the $_timezone member, but it would be nice if one could manually modify the $_offset parameter using some getters and setters.  In contrast, it would also be nice to be able to give setTimeZone something other than the PHP timezones (more along the lines of \"-7\" or \"GMT+0600\").  My reasoning for wanting to set the $_offset member myself are that I can get a unix timestamp for the server, and a unix timestamp for the client, so I can get the value of $_offset, but I can't easily get a value that setTimeZone likes."
        },
