        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23507",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "No, there will be no setter\/getter for this private property, because there are dependencies on other members.\n\nOffset is used for holding the offset for the servers time to the real time when using Zend_TimeSync.\n\nWhen creating a date object you can simply set Timezones by setting a real timezone along the olson database, or a windows timezone using Zend_Locale or simply an hour offset like +0600 or -02:00 by using the proper input formats.\n\nAnyhow you calculate this, you must give an hour offset. All other things will not be recognised as Timezone setting as timezones are ALWAYS hour offsets.\n\nThere is also a getTimezoneByString method which could be handy.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-16T01:50:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-16T01:50:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23508",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Feature would corrupt other features necessary for date calculation.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-16T01:51:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-16T01:51:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23526",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=admwiggin",
                        "name": "admwiggin",
                        "displayName": "Tianon Gravi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I couldn't convince setTimezone to accept any kind of hour offset (even in formats like 'UTC+0800' or 'UTC-7'), so my solution ended up being looping over the list returned by timezone_abbreviations_list() and just using the first timezone_id that had the offset I was looking for. This isn't the best solution, but it's the best I could come up with to just allow me to adjust my Zend_Date objects into the offset I want\/need.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=admwiggin",
                        "name": "admwiggin",
                        "displayName": "Tianon Gravi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-18T08:30:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-18T08:30:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23528",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=admwiggin",
                        "name": "admwiggin",
                        "displayName": "Tianon Gravi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Long story short, timezone_abbreviations_list() doesn't really work too well.  Too many duplicates with different offsets.\n\ntimezone_name_from_abbr, however, works like a charm:\n\n<?php\necho timezone_name_from_abbr('', -25200, 0);\n\/\/ prints out \"America\/Denver\"",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=admwiggin",
                        "name": "admwiggin",
                        "displayName": "Tianon Gravi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-18T10:37:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-18T10:37:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23529",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Timezones in date strings are eighter defined as timezone name for example \"America\/Denver\" or as hour offset for example \"+0800\".\n\nBoth are recognised by Zend_Date and the mentioned getTimezoneByString method.\n\nTimezones by second offset are not allowed and therefor not supported.\nYou can simply come around this by dividing 25200 by 3600 and use this as input for the houroffset.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-18T11:35:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-18T11:35:11.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
